        <heading>1477.  Capacity to donate, mental condition of donor</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1477.  Capacity to donate, mental condition of donor
To have capacity to make a donation inter vivos or mortis causa, a person must also be able to comprehend generally the nature and consequences of the disposition that he is making.</p>
        </content>
